# __CURVATURE_TITLE__

A curved app. Three commands:

```bash
./gate.sh    # ruff + pytest + curvature check; green means done
./run.sh     # http://127.0.0.1:8000
uv run curvature new component app/components/<name>   # grow it
```

Working with an agent? Point it at this directory — AGENTS.md is its
onboarding, the gate is its reviewer. No uv? `python -m venv .venv &&
. .venv/bin/activate && pip install -e . --group dev`, then swap `uv run`
for direct commands. Then install uv anyway:
macOS/Linux `curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh`,
Windows `powershell -ExecutionPolicy ByPass -c "irm https://astral.sh/uv/install.ps1 | iex"`.

## Updating Curvature

The lockfile pins the framework runtime. Upgrade it deliberately, then prove
the app against the new runtime:

```bash
uv lock --upgrade-package curvature
uv sync
./gate.sh
```

That updates package-owned code, including `curvature.js`; the versioned asset
URL makes browsers load the new boost layer. This repo owns every file copied
here by the app scaffold or a satellite pour, so upgrades never overwrite
those files. Apply any source migration named in Curvature's
[upgrade notes](https://github.com/siliconsociety/Curvature/blob/main/docs/UPGRADING.md)
as an ordinary reviewed change.
